file_content.text: Oh, boy.
The lift's not coming, is it?
Not responding?
Oh, no, it's coming. It's just not empty.
The lift's on its way, but I didn't call it. Somebody's coming to see us off.
Vaylin. I can sense her presence.
Time for Plan B.
What's Plan B?
Run and hope for a Plan C.
What about the escape pods, or calling back the tanker to pick us up?
There has to be something.
Too slow, not to mention it's our only bargaining chip if we get caught, and I'd rather wind up caught than take your other suggestion.
I was expecting something a bit more concrete.
That's it?
There's being prepared and being psychic. For lack of a crystal ball, we'll have to improvise.
I'm tired of running from Vaylin.
Let's fight.
Well I've got a few laps left in me.
Even if you win, and don't turn the Skyhook into crumbled wreckage, we'll still be surrounded by thousands of her flunkeys.
There is no around.
There is out there.
You want us to scale the exterior?
Pretty much. Look, there's no time to stand here arguing, so I recommend lodging your complaints at a steady jog.
Ah, it's not so bad. Just don't look down or consider your own mortality.
Goodbye, Spewie. I'll never forget you!
We'd never be seen again down in that murk. The Skyhook's still the best option, there's just the matter of getting on.
We have to go around.
